== <span style="font-family:Jost">Description ==
{{Blurimage|file=919-2-1.png|caption=First ever photograph of Level 919}}Level 919 is an expansive architectural world built above a seemingly infinite body of water. Walkways, halls and arched entries constructed of white stone or metal connect this level, floating above and partially resting on still bodies of black water. The air is cool and slightly dense as if electrically charged, but not in a harmful or uncomfortable way—in a slightly unfamiliar one. There is no scent except for something akin to ozone. Above is an endless night, although white lights emit from within the walkways and walls and depressions within the larger structures, bathing the creations of this level in a garish light.

{{Blurimage|file=919-2-2.png|caption=Marble bridges connect the floating floors}}Postmodern Architecture reigns supreme—minimalism in symmetrical, repetitive designs. The buildings do not decay, nor do they boast illegible or symbolic signage or decoration; some buildings are unenterable with no doors or windows, and some are weigh stations that lead to large, void rooms or expansive halls with nothing but more space inside.

{{Blurimage|file=919-2-3.png|caption=The architecture of the level; with triangular arches and slopes}}There is no sun or moon. There is a constant twilight. There is no horizon to the expansive black water surrounding each entrance to access this world; it is still and seemingly endless. No one who has traveled has ever come back from having explored to the bottom or edge of anything. Going too far just results in disorientation and immediate transportation back to the center of the level.

{{Blurimage|file=919-2-4.png|caption=Level photographed in a brightest twilight (phenomenon).}}The white walkways of Level 919 are thin and precarious, connecting some sections to the next by giant support beams and others hovering just above the water level. While many of the pathways feature a groove down the center, a majority of which constitutes a canal that flows with crystalline water, the pathways of Level 919 provide hydration—albeit no one knows whence it springs.

A notable round platform at the seeming center of the level with a high, warped obelisk form. The nearby structures are more elaborate and include columns, pointed towers, and ribbon-like shapes that appear to have no use. Some visitors say that this location emits soft harmonic tones.

Some raised walkways connect to rooms with big, square apertures looking out over the remainder of the level. Though unfurnished, these rooms are clean and temperature-controlled. Some have idle consoles or dark projectors generating low mechanical noises.

==<span style="font-family:Jost"> "Black Water" ==
{{Blurimage|file=Black Water.png|caption=Black waters of Level 919, in its liquid form.}}The '''"Black Water"''', is a dense, opaque liquid substance observed in large quantities throughout Level 919. It fills the canals, reservoirs, and surrounding bodies within the level's architecture. The substance is visually characterized by its black-blue coloration, high viscosity, and complete absence of reflectivity under both artificial and ambient lighting.

Black Water is not water in the conventional chemical sense. Preliminary analyses indicate an anomalous molecular composition, with non-H₂O base elements and anti-reflective particulate matter suspended throughout. Samples collected lose anomalous properties once removed from Level 919, breaking down into a gelatinous soot-like residue.

== <span style="font-family:Jost">Entities  ==
Entities such as [[Entity 3|Smilers]] and [[Entity 3-A|Frowners]] inhabit Level 919. However, wanderers have occasionally reported shadows on the far ends of bridges or movement within the walls of solid buildings. These claims remain unverified, and no aggressive behavior or evidence has been recorded.

== <span style="font-family:Jost">Additional Notes ==

* Prolonged exposure (48+ hours) may lead to “Architectural Displacement Syndrome” which is a term used for mild spatial memory loss and a distorted sense of direction. This is temporary and wears off after exiting the level.
* No night or day cycle has been observed.
* The materials of the structures are smooth, cool to the touch, and resistant to damage or alteration.
* It is unknown if the level is artificial or naturally occurring.

== <span style="font-family:Jost">Entrances & Exits </span> ==

=== <span style="font-family:Jost">Entrances</span> ===

* Noclipping through a mirrored surface in [[Level 56]] has a small chance of transporting wanderers to '''Level 919.'''
* Drowning in the waters of [[Level 37.1]] can you bring one here.

* Noclipping a picture depicting the Poolrooms in [[Level 918]] is theorized to lead here.
* Noclipping into a picture of the Poolrooms in [[Level 450]] leads here.
=== <span style="font-family:Jost">Exits </span> ===

* Noclipping beneath the walkways into the dark water may lead to [[Level 2]]
* Walking a continuous straight line across ten bridges without deviating may transport a wanderer to [[Level 231]] or return them to [[Level 0]] (rare).

